<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1292,1823]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,1472,1498]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">General distribution.</emphasis>
The Lesser Antilles, 
<collectingCountry box="[684,774,1472,1498]" name="Guyana" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[784,894,1472,1498]" name="Suriname" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Suriname</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[904,975,1472,1498]" name="Brazil" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[986,1040,1473,1499]" name="Peru" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1050,1135,1472,1498]" name="Bolivia" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1250,1473,1499]" name="Paraguay" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, Argentina (
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Nessimian, J. L." pageId="37" pageNumber="488" pagination="101 - 130" refId="ref46774" refString="Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. (2013) The genus Buenoa Kirkaldy, 1904 (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Nepomorpha: Notonectidae) in northern Brazil: inventory, new records, and new species. Zootaxa, 3694 (2), 101 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3694.2.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Barbosa &amp; Nessimian 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1292,1823]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1544,1570]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1904" box="[304,517,1545,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Buenoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amnigenus">
<emphasis box="[304,517,1545,1570]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Buenoa amnigenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found in the margins of ditches, drains, mangrove swamps, pools, ponds, and natural and artificial lakes, mostly exposed to sunlight and with floating, emergent, submerged vegetation and rivers (
<bibRefCitation author="Truxal, F. S." box="[230,372,1616,1643]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" pagination="1351 - 1523" refId="ref58751" refString="Truxal, F. S. (1953) A revision of the genus Buenoa (Hemiptera, Notonectidae). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 35, 1351 - 1523." type="journal article" year="1953">Truxal 1953</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser, N." box="[385,525,1616,1643]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" pagination="1 - 310" refId="ref54944" refString="Nieser, N. (1975) The water bugs (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha) of the Guyana Region. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 16, 1 - 310. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 017 - 7118 - 4 _ 1" type="journal article" year="1975">Nieser 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser, N. &amp; Alkins-Koo, M." box="[537,845,1616,1642]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" pagination="1 - 127" refId="ref55079" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Alkins-Koo, M. (1991) The water bugs of Trinidad &amp; Tobago. Occasional Papers, Department of Zoology, University of the West Indies, 9, i - iii + 1 - 127." type="journal article" year="1991">Nieser &amp; Alkins-Koo 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Nessimian, J. L." box="[857,1173,1616,1642]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" pagination="101 - 130" refId="ref46774" refString="Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. (2013) The genus Buenoa Kirkaldy, 1904 (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Nepomorpha: Notonectidae) in northern Brazil: inventory, new records, and new species. Zootaxa, 3694 (2), 101 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3694.2.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Barbosa &amp; Nessimian 2013</bibRefCitation>
). It has also been taken at lights (
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser, N." box="[255,396,1652,1679]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" pagination="1 - 310" refId="ref54944" refString="Nieser, N. (1975) The water bugs (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha) of the Guyana Region. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 16, 1 - 310. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 017 - 7118 - 4 _ 1" type="journal article" year="1975">Nieser 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Nessimian, J. L." box="[408,722,1652,1678]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" pagination="101 - 130" refId="ref46774" refString="Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. (2013) The genus Buenoa Kirkaldy, 1904 (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Nepomorpha: Notonectidae) in northern Brazil: inventory, new records, and new species. Zootaxa, 3694 (2), 101 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3694.2.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Barbosa &amp; Nessimian 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1292,1823]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
At the INR, specimens were collected from the margins of the Iberá Lagoon in shallow waters with emergent and floating vegetation (Estévez 
<emphasis box="[514,567,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">et al.</emphasis>
2003). During the present study, this species was collected in flood-prone areas (together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1904" box="[311,411,1760,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Buenoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salutis">
<emphasis box="[311,411,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">B. salutis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and streams with unshaded margins and with dense emergent vegetation. Additional specimens of this species were taken at lights in San Ignacio Ranger Station and Laguna Iberá Ranger Station.
</paragraph>
